🤸🏻‍♀️ 🌸 S O L D 🌟 🤸🏼‍♂️ To some very special buyers - US!! 🥰 So excited to close on a home together, to start our new chapter as a married couple @jmaya24 💕 👰🏻‍♀️ 🏡 🤵🏻‍♂️ 
•
This home is a special milestone for us for many reasons. Though this will be house number 5 for us in our growing portfolio, it is the first one that we have closed on together, and the first one that we will be calling home as a family 😊. For nearly two years, we have been trying to settle into a house together, but THREE (yes, 3) cross-country moves got in the way. We are so happy to be planting roots down in Houston, TX.
•
I am a firm believer that purchasing/investing in real estate as early as you can, will unlock exponentially more financial opportunities down the road, which will hopefully lead to early retirement. We have two long-term rentals that have appreciated significantly over the last 5 years (one of which reached positive cash flow in year 3), and two successful Airbnb’s with minimal upfront cash investment. Because we were able to leverage our debt and assets, and strategically structure our businesses, we’ve been able to leapfrog over many years of saving to purchase more property. You can achieve great things with determination and an open mind!
•
If you want to learn more on how to start building significant wealth through real estate, give me a call ☎️ 484-347-4093

🌟 S O L D 🌟  A little late on the post, but so happy for this amazing couple to have a piece of Houston to call their own upon relocating here from Sunny San Diego! 
•
This transaction was *not easy* - a lot of negotiating back and forth with a relocation company and several  underwriting challenges with complex 1099 nuances over the course of 11 weeks. I truly believe that most lenders and agents would have given up, but determination, persistence, and emergency CPA two days before Christmas, and some creativity pulled this to the closing table! I am truly so fortunate to have amazing clients who persevered, and an amazing lender who pulled all the strings possible to make this happen. I can thankfully say I don’t think I will ever work on a transaction through two emergency room visits and my own wedding ever again 🤣 🏆 CONGRATS Bri and Devon, and welcome home!!

Crispy rice paper pork dumplings 👩🏻‍🍳 🔥 🥟 You can easily make this vegetarian by omitting the pork and oyster sauce
•
These were so fun and easy to make! My secret @heb hack below:
⭐️ one package @HEB sweet Asian salad kit (it has chopped cabbage, carrots and cilantro!)
⭐️ one lb ground pork
⭐️ one package umami mushroom mix, chopped (about 1-2 cups)
⭐️ two tbs chopped garlic
⭐️ one package rice paper
⭐️ 1 tbs minced ginger
⭐️ oyster sauce, salt and sesame oil to taste
•
🥢 sauté the garlic and chopped mushrooms for about 5 mins over medium heat
🥢 mix pork and the salad kit (veggies only), with about 2 tbs oyster sauce, 1 tsp salt, 1-2 tsp sesame oil
🥢 Add the pork and veggie mix into the same pan with the mushrooms and cook over medium heat until pork is cooked through 
🥢 Dip two sheets of rice paper into a bowl of water for about 2 secs, then separate and lay flat on a cutting board 
🥢 Spoon a loose 1/4c of the cooked filling mixture into one rice paper, and fold all four sides, one at a time, overlapping in the center. Should look like a cute little spring roll package. Take the rolled rice “dumpling”, folds side down, and lay it into the next rice paper and repeat so that it is double-wrapped in rice paper 
🥢 Heat up olive oil about 1/4 inch deep into the pan  on high heat until shimmering - fry up the rice paper dumplings in both sides until crispy and golden brown
🥢 Enjoy! I like to dip mine in dumpling sauce and topped with a little Szechuan chili oil
